Barcelona have opened talks with Wolves over a deal to re-sign Spain winger Adama Traore. The Catalan club wants an initial loan deal with an obligation to buy at the end of the season. The move ends Tottenham’s hopes of signing the 26-year-old, who began his career at Barcelona. BBC Sport understands Antonio Conte’s side had a £15m bid for Traore rejected last week, although sources at the London club deny making an offer.   CAF moves three Cup of Nations games from Douala to Yaounde     Mo Salah spot kick sends Egypt to Q-Finals     Sadio Mane upbeat after concussion against Cape Verde   - Advertisement - Traore has 18 months left on his contract at Molineux and talks over a new deal that have yet to reach an agreement. He left the Nou Camp for Aston Villa in 2015 and spent two years at Middlesbrough before joining Wolves for a then club-record £18m in 2018. The winger has made 154 appearances for the Black Country club, scoring 11 goals. Wolves are yet to decide whether they will strengthen their squad following the arrival of Chiquinho from Estoril last week. BBC